Subject: Vendor strategy on your real-time data stack — the open-source option

Board questions about long-term vendor exposure on a DataStax-backed stack are coming up more often since the IBM acquisition. It's a reasonable thing to pressure-test, especially at Capital One's scale.

ScyllaDB is Apache 2.0 licensed, community-governed, and not owned by a cloud provider. For teams running real-time transaction processing at scale, that's become a meaningful part of the evaluation — not just the performance numbers.

The technical migration from DataStax to ScyllaDB is straightforward: CQL-compatible, same drivers, existing data files transfer without conversion. The operational risk is low.

